metadata.dc:description: Although complications post-URS are scant and can usually be resolved by conservative methods, these however, may be potentially severe as in the present case in whom a ureteroiliac fistula was observed during a URS procedure that had been performed to dilate a post-URS stenosis. Previously, extravasation had also occurred. The post-URS complications are briefly described and discussed.
metadata.dc:title: Fístula ureteroiliaca como una complicación de ureterorrenoscopia.
[Ureteroiliac fistula as a complication of ureterorenoscopy].
